Declarations
------------

par p1
par p2, p3, p4

Definitions
-----------

p1 := astring                       /* Simple */
p2 := several strins                /* Set parameter */
p3 #= source, regexp, replacement   /* Parameter copy / replace */
p4 %= regexp                        /* File matching */

grash p1:astring p2:"several strings" < script.g /* Definition at invocation */

Actions
-------

Action      := Cmd | Primitive | Sequence | Alternative | Set
Primitive   := ( Action Arg1 Arg2 .. )
Sequence    := ( Action && Action && .. )
Alternative := ( Action || Action || .. )
Set         := ( BoundVariable <- SetVariable: Action )

Program
-------

A program consists of:

1. Declarations of all used variables
2. Variable definitions (some could be defined via the command line parameters)
3. A number of actions
